nation has
had turbulent relations with the
Obama White

32:44.296 --> 32:51.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
House since the 2011 revolution,
and the subsequent
2013 coup that first brought
El-Sisi to power.

32:51.570 --> 32:56.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Egypt's foreign minister, Sameh
Shoukry, has
been in Washington meeting with
Secretary

32:56.341 --> 33:01.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of State Kerry and with key
leaders on Capitol
Hill, and last week with vice
president-elect

33:01.746 --> 33:03.515 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Mike Pence.

33:03.548 --> 33:06.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This morning, he sat down with
our chief foreign
affairs correspondent, Margaret
Warner.

33:06.785 --> 33:10.856 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Minister
Shoukry, thank you
so much for having us.

33:10.889 --> 33:15.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President-elect Trump and your
President Sisi
have had some very glowing words
to say about

33:15.594 --> 33:17.295 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
one another.

33:17.329 --> 33:20.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Your own embassy just put out a
statement
that, in fact, you are looking
forward to

33:20.165 --> 33:22.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
better ties with the new
administration.

33:22.133 --> 33:26.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, are you looking forward to
turning the
page on this U.S.-Egypt
relationship, which

33:26.905 --> 33:28.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has had its ups and downs over
the last few
years?

33:28.874 --> 33:32.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY, Egyptian Foreign
Minister:
We're certainly looking forward
for consolidating

33:32.577 --> 33:34.579 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and strengthening the
U.S.-Egyptian relationship.

33:34.613 --> 33:39.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is always our objective to
have close ties
with the United States.

33:39.117 --> 33:45.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're at a transitional period
of our history
and we're on a road to reform.

33:45.123 --> 33:48.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: How do you
expect the Trump
administration to be different
than the Obama

33:48.960 --> 33:50.896 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
administration when it comes to
dealing with
Egypt?

33:50.929 --> 33:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: Well, we look
forward, from
what we heard from
president-elect Trump,

33:55.166 --> 34:00.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a clear vision related to the
conditions and
the challenges in the Middle
East.

34:00.572 --> 34:05.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there's a great deal of
parallelity in
that vision related to how we
can eradicate

34:05.777 --> 34:08.013 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
terrorism, how we can regain
stability in
the region.

34:08.046 --> 34:13.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: So, are you
expecting more
cooperation on fighting
terrorism or making

34:13.418 --> 34:17.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that the priority, and less
attention, for
example, to the issue of human
rights in Egypt?

34:17.789 --> 34:20.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: That's not the
issue that concerns
us.

34:20.558 --> 34:27.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think the issue that concerns
us is certainly
regaining stability, but issues
of human rights

34:27.232 --> 34:31.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are an integral part of our
reform policies,
of our new constitution.

34:31.970 --> 34:37.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Did either Mr.
Trump or Mr.
Pence, when you met with vice
president-elect

34:37.108 --> 34:40.545 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pence, on their own raise the
issue of human
rights with you?

34:40.578 --> 34:45.684 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: On the occasion
of my meeting,
it was to convey a message from
President

34:45.717 --> 34:47.485 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Sisi.

34:47.519 --> 34:53.658 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And there was a general
discussion related
to conditions in the region and
the importance

34:53.692 --> 34:57.862 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the strategic relationship
that binds the
United States and Egypt.

34:57.896 --> 34:59.064 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: But what about
human rights?

34:59.097 --> 35:00.932 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: It wasn't raised
specifically.

35:00.966 --> 35:02.534 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: It wasn't
raised specifically?

35:02.567 --> 35:04.035 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: No.

35:04.069 --> 35:07.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: There is one
case that is
getting some attention here.

35:07.205 --> 35:14.980 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's of a young woman
named Aya Hijazi,
who came to work with her
husband in a sort

35:15.013 --> 35:16.715 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of center for street kids.

35:16.748 --> 35:21.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then she's been arrested and
held for
months and months on what
everyone here says

35:21.519 --> 35:24.589 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is bogus charges that they were
abusing the
children.

35:24.622 --> 35:26.191 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What is the status of that case?

35:26.224 --> 35:30.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: Well, I think
it's a very serious
accusation that's been made.

35:30.495 --> 35:36.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think anyone would be
interested to
get to the bottom of accusations
related to

35:36.267 --> 35:38.503 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
minors and related to abuse.

35:38.536 --> 35:43.641 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, I would challenge the issue
of bogus accusations.

35:43.675 --> 35:49.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think it's important to
recognize the
impartiality of the Egyptian
judicial system.

35:49.414 --> 35:52.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: So, let me ask
you a couple
of other things about human
rights.

35:52.951 --> 35:58.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Your Parliament last week just
passed another
law, further restrictions on the
rights or

35:58.189 --> 36:00.892 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the activities of NGOs.

36:00.925 --> 36:03.094 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Will President Sisi sign that?

36:03.128 --> 36:10.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: The elected
officials decided
that they had their own vision
of what they

36:10.869 --> 36:13.004 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
considered in the best interests
of the public.

36:13.038 --> 36:19.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this was just before I left,
so I don't
have any information related to
what the president's

36:19.110 --> 36:20.912 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
position on it is.

36:20.945 --> 36:24.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: As you know,
human rights
are a deep concern here in the
United States

36:24.883 --> 36:26.618 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in terms of what's going on in
Egypt.

36:26.651 --> 36:31.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it is hard for people to
understand why
so many dissidents, journalists,
activists,

36:31.623 --> 36:38.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nonviolent people, NGOs, have
been rounded
up, are being detained, are
having their rights

36:38.863 --> 36:44.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
restricted, why, for people who
speak out,
for people who want to
demonstrate.

36:44.869 --> 36:45.837 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: My -- exactly.

36:45.870 --> 36:48.006 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's not a matter of people
speaking out.

36:48.039 --> 36:55.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's nobody who's been
accused of anything
related to freedom of expression
or undertaking

36:55.547 --> 36:57.916 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
activities of civic
responsibility.

36:57.949 --> 37:05.490 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
All those who have been
subjected to a judicial
inquiry and trials have been
accused of criminal

37:05.523 --> 37:11.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
