38:08.186 --> 38:11.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was referring to the fact
that we consider
that it is the national armies
of the nation

38:11.656 --> 38:14.759 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
state which are responsible to
fight terrorism.

38:14.792 --> 38:16.861 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That is their primary
responsibility.

38:16.895 --> 38:21.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have the better ability,
rather than
relying on any form of foreign
intervention

38:21.799 --> 38:23.601 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in this regard.

38:23.635 --> 38:29.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we believe that a political
solution should
be under way, and that which is
necessarily

38:29.674 --> 38:32.810 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
inclusive of all political
factions in Syria.

38:32.844 --> 38:38.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there is no commitment
towards any specific
political entity in Syria.

38:38.183 --> 38:42.086 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There hasn't been any reference
to the current
Syrian government.

38:42.120 --> 38:47.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: So, would you
say your position
is closer to that of the United
States or

38:47.158 --> 38:48.960 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
-- right now -- or to Russia?

38:48.993 --> 38:52.063 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: We have been
cooperating with
both the United States and
Russia, have been

38:52.096 --> 38:57.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
actively supporting a greater
understanding
between them because of their
ability to impact

38:57.702 --> 38:59.504 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the situation.

38:59.537 --> 39:04.008 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We believe that it is
intolerable that the
current level of violence and --
that we continue

39:04.042 --> 39:09.781 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
after five years of a
half-a-million loss
of life, that we -- that this
situation should

39:09.814 --> 39:11.449 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
continue.

39:11.482 --> 39:14.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Let me end with
asking you
about a couple of campaign
promises.

39:14.385 --> 39:19.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President-elect Trump said he
was going to
push to renegotiate this entire
Iran nuclear

39:19.891 --> 39:20.858 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
deal.

39:20.892 --> 39:21.826 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Do you think that's a good idea?

39:21.859 --> 39:24.395 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: The issue is very
important.

39:24.429 --> 39:28.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we must guarantee that the
region remains
free of nuclear weapons.

39:29.000 --> 39:33.238 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: And so do you
think the Iran
nuclear deal furthers that aim?

39:33.271 --> 39:39.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: We believe that
the deal can
-- has room for improvement,
definitely, in

39:39.410 --> 39:45.283 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
terms of the time and in terms
of the guarantees
to prevent any proliferation of
nuclear weapons.

39:45.316 --> 39:49.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: And then,
finally, he promised
to move the U.S. Embassy -- this
is an old

39:49.687 --> 39:51.856 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
issue -- from Tel Aviv to
Jerusalem.

39:51.890 --> 39:53.958 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Would that be high on your list?

39:53.992 --> 39:55.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: No.

39:55.793 --> 40:01.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have always opposed any
movement in that
direction as contravening
international law

40:01.299 --> 40:02.267 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and legitimacy.

40:02.300 --> 40:06.704 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Thank you very
much, sir.

40:06.738 --> 40:13.378 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SAMEH SHOUKRY: Thank you.

40:13.411 --> 40:20.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Protesters won a
big 11th-hour
victory from the Obama
administration yesterday

40:20.885 --> 40:25.156 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that prevents the completion of
the Dakota
Access pipeline.

40:25.189 --> 40:29.827 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But is it just a temporary delay
until president-elect
Trump takes office?

40:29.861 --> 40:35.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The nearly 1,200-mile pipeline
was almost
complete before this weekend's
announcement.

40:35.266 --> 40:40.505 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the last stretches is a
single-mile
segment that goes under the
Missouri River.

40:40.538 --> 40:43.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The battle has been raging for
seven months
now.

40:43.574 --> 40:45.376 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And to Hari Sreenivasan for our
update.

40:45.410 --> 40:48.012 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: The Corps of Engineers is
going to deny
the easement.

40:48.046 --> 40:49.947 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

40:49.981 --> 40:55.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Thousands of
protesters
celebrated the announcement late
yesterday.

40:55.820 --> 41:00.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Sunday, the U.S. Army Corps
of Engineers
said it wouldn't grant the final
easement

41:00.958 --> 41:03.428 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to allow the pipeline to be
drilled.

41:03.461 --> 41:07.598 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Instead, the Corps said it would
begin exploring
alternative routes.

41:07.632 --> 41:12.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Standing Rock Sioux tribe
and others say
the pipeline will destroy sacred
lands and

41:12.270 --> 41:16.274 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are worried an oil leak could
threaten the
tribe's water supply.

41:16.307 --> 41:20.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
North Dakota's governor, the
company and members
of the state's congressional
delegation all

41:20.945 --> 41:22.714 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
denounced the decision.

41:22.747 --> 41:25.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
William Brangham has been
covering the story
for months, and is with us again
tonight.

41:25.850 --> 41:28.252 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William, this doesn't seem to be
over.

41:28.286 --> 41:30.722 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't see the protesters
breaking camp.

41:30.755 --> 41:32.523 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't see anybody jumping for
joy.

41:32.557 --> 41:34.359 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: No.

41:34.392 --> 41:38.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was some joy certainly
yesterday, and
I think, obviously, some
spillover into today,

41:38.830 --> 41:42.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because, for many people, this
was considered
an enormous victory.

41:42.100 --> 41:46.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is what the Standing Rock
tribe and all
of its thousands of supporters
have wanted

41:46.104 --> 41:50.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for months, which was to stop
the pipeline
going under the Missouri River
right next

41:50.575 --> 41:51.676 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to the tribe.

41:51.709 --> 41:54.445 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, whether this is over or not
is still
an issue.

41:54.479 --> 41:56.514 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Army Corps didn't cancel the
pipeline.

41:56.547 --> 41:59.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They didn't say it's definitely
not going
here.

41:59.083 --> 42:03.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They said, let's take a longer
review, let's
talk to the tribes some more,
and let's consider

42:03.988 --> 42:05.490 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
some alternate routes.

42:05.523 --> 42:08.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it's still not clear if this
is, in fact,
the done deal.

42:08.926 --> 42:12.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And the
alternate route
idea doesn't sit well with the
local authorities

42:12.997 --> 42:13.965 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and the company.

42:13.998 --> 42:15.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: No.

42:15.800 --> 42:18.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The company has, from the very
beginning,
been steadfast that they will
not move this

42:18.903 --> 42:20.438 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
pipeline.

42:20.471 --> 42:23.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The governor of North Dakota has
said the
pipeline is not going to be
moved.

42:23.908 --> 42:28.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, the Army Corps of Engineers
could and
has in the past looked at other
routes.

42:28.780 --> 42:31.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's multiple ways to cross
the Missouri
River here.

42:31.315 --> 42:35.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But right now, the Army Corps of
Engineers
says all options are open and
they're going

42:35.386 --> 42:37.221 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
back to the drawing board, in
essence.

42:37.255 --> 42:41.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: So, what
happens to the
protesters in the coldest part
of winter heading

42:41.793 --> 42:43.161 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
into this area now?

42:43.194 --> 42:45.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Well, that's
still an open
question.

42:45.263 --> 42:47.231 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We don't know yet.

42:47.265 --> 42:52.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The head of the Standing Rock
Sioux, the chairman,
David Archambault Ii, he, in
essence, declared

42:52.303 --> 42:56.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this as a victory, and he said,
people, you
can go home now, things are
safe.

42:56.674 --> 43:01.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, in the back of their
minds, they
know that, just as the Obama
administration

43:01.045 --> 43:04.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
made this happen, a Trump
administration might
try to reverse course.

43:04.348 --> 43:07.852 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, I think everyone is
recognizing subzero
temperatures.

43:07.885 --> 43:12.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is a very, very hard place
to live out
in the open on the prairies of
North Dakota.

43:12.657 --> 43:14.125 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's freezing.

43:14.158 --> 43:16.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, everyone, go home, rest,
that's what the
chairman seems to be saying.

43:16.794 --> 43:19.664 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if we need to call on you
again, we will
do so.

43:19.697 --> 43:23.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Is there any
indication
that the policy change after the
inauguration

43:23.534 --> 43:24.502 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Donald Trump?

43:24.535 --> 43:26.237 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Well,
certainly.

43:26.270 --> 43:29.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's -- this was, in essence,
driven in
large part by pressure brought
to bear on

43:29.941 --> 43:34.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Obama administration and
them asking the
Army Corps to take a second look
at this.

43:35.012 --> 43:39.951 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, what the Obama
administration has done,
the Trump administration could
undo.

43:39.984 --> 43:43.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Trump has been very clear
from the get-go
he wants this pipeline to be
built.

43:44.021 --> 43:48.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And that tribe
has had a,
well, complicated relationship
with the Army

43:48.292 --> 43:51.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Corps, this particular decision
that they
support, but, in the past,
there's a lot of

43:51.462 --> 43:52.497 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
decisions that they have not.

43:52.530 --> 43:54.265 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That's
correct.

43:54.298 --> 43:57.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, there have been a lot of
instances
where the tribe has said, we
have not been

43:57.668 --> 43:59.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
consulted on these types of
events in the
past.

43:59.837 --> 44:04.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, one of the biggest
critics of this
is a Congressman Kevin Cramer
from North Dakota.

44:04.775 --> 44:09.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He points out, good luck on
trying to do any
infrastructure projects in the
U.S. going

44:09.580 --> 44:11.516 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
forward, if you can simply
overturn it like
this.

44:11.549 --> 44:17.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he says, on this very same
land, natural
gas pipelines have been put
through, electric

44:17.288 --> 44:19.757 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
high-tension power lines have
gone through.

44:19.790 --> 44:23.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the tribe wasn't happy about
that, but
they said that they had no power
to do anything

44:23.361 --> 44:25.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about it, whereas, with this
pipeline, they
did.

44:25.730 --> 44:31.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Just recently,
there was
audio of the conversations that
took place

44:31.035 --> 44:35.273 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and where the tribe was
considering this,
because one of the contentions
that the tribe

44:35.306 --> 44:37.642 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
had is that: We were not part of
this process.

44:37.675 --> 44:38.643 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

44:38.676 --> 44:40.511 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That's right.

44:40.545 --> 44:42.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The audio that you're referring
to is an instance
of several years ago, where the
tribe made

44:42.880 --> 44:47.585 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
very clear that they didn't want
this pipeline
coming anywhere near them.

44:47.618 --> 44:52.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem with that is that,
in subsequent
meetings, the Army Corps has
been saying:

44:52.890 --> 44:56.861 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have asked for the tribe to
continue to
offer further input.

44:56.894 --> 45:01.832 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they argue that they simply
didn't respond
and that they didn't come to
subsequent meetings.

45:01.866 --> 45:05.202 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think it's been quite
clear the tribe
has been against this from the
get-go.

45:05.236 --> 45:09.206 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
William Brangham,
thanks so much.

45:09.240 --> 45:16.914 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Thanks, Hari.

45:16.948 --> 45:24.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally tonight:
It's North
America's biggest art fair, with
big money

45:24.822 --> 45:29.193 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at stake, but who is it for and
how does it
work?

45:29.226 --> 45:34.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown visited Miami
Beach to find
out what Art Basel is all about,
which just

45:34.332 --> 45:36.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wrapped up this weekend.

45:36.334 --> 45:42.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A family reunion
for the international
art tribe, a trade show, but one
that includes

45:42.807 --> 45:49.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some up-to-the-moment political
commentary,
Art Basel Miami Beach is all of
that and more,

45:49.447 --> 45:55.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
art of all shapes and sizes and
colors and
kinds, and all for sale.

45:55.186 --> 46:00.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It can be head-spinning, or, if
you're a prominent
gallery owner like Jack
Shainman, nightmare-inducing:

46:00.491 --> 46:07.164 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK SHAINMAN, Jack Shainman
Gallery: A lot
happens the first days or the
first few hours.

46:07.198 --> 46:13.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, one of my anxiety
dreams that I have
when I travel is that all these
collectors

46:13.170 --> 46:17.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
show up at my booth at the same
time at an
art fair, and I can't talk to
all of them

46:17.642 --> 46:19.543 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
at once.

46:19.577 --> 46:24.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Here at the Miami
Beach Convention
Center, 269 high-end galleries
from 29 countries

46:24.582 --> 46:31.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
around the world take part in
the main art
fair, last year attracting
95,000 viewers

46:31.122 --> 46:33.691 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and collectors over six days.

46:33.724 --> 46:35.326 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Fred Bidwell was back this year.

46:35.359 --> 46:37.662 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED BIDWELL, Art Collector:
This is crazy.

46:37.695 --> 46:41.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is more art than the human
mind could
possibly perceive.

46:41.232 --> 46:47.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: With billions of
dollars on
the line, including new money
from abroad,

46:47.238 --> 46:50.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
New York gallery owners James
and Jane Cohan
have a lot at stake.

46:50.908 --> 46:55.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE COHAN, James Cohan Gallery:
We really
know the kinds of things our
clients are looking

46:55.079 --> 46:56.947 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for.

46:56.981 --> 46:59.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when we have something
that's spectacular,
they have been interested in a
certain artist,

46:59.450 --> 47:02.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we have a spectacular work,
we're going to
let them know that we're
bringing it to the

47:02.153 --> 47:04.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fair, and then they can come and
see it.

47:04.221 --> 47:06.724 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, a little bit
of this is
sort of precooked?

47:06.757 --> 47:08.559 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JANE COHAN: Absolutely.

47:08.592 --> 47:12.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I still really believe that
you have to
see a work of art in person to
fall in love.

47:12.730 --> 47:17.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Collectors come
in all forms,
trophy hunters, speculators, and
actual lovers

47:17.835 --> 47:19.737 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of art.

47:19.770 --> 47:24.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This fair, an offshoot of one in
Basel, Switzerland,
is known for attracting Latin
American art

47:24.909 --> 47:30.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and collectors, including Tiqui
Atencio, who's
just written a book about
collecting art.

47:30.448 --> 47:33.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIQUI ATENCIO, Art Collector: I
walked into
a gallery that I love, which is
the Brazilian

47:34.018 --> 47:36.787 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gallery from Sao Paulo, Fontes
de Deloya (ph).

47:36.821 --> 47:43.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I started looking around,
and I saw these
two wonderful Latin American
artists from

47:43.227 --> 47:45.262 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Brazil in their 20s.

47:45.296 --> 47:46.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I thought, oh, my God, these
are fantastic
artists.

47:46.297 --> 47:47.698 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And did you buy?

47:47.732 --> 47:50.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TIQUI ATENCIO: I'm thinking of
it.

47:50.034 --> 47:51.736 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

47:51.769 --> 47:55.606 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Fifteen years in,
Art Basel
Miami has spawned more than 20
additional

47:55.639 --> 48:01.345 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
local fairs, catering to
different styles
and wallets, including one
titled Untitled.

48:01.378 --> 48:03.781 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: There's a lot to see,
yes.

48:03.814 --> 48:09.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: With so much to
see, art advisers
have become big players here and
elsewhere

48:09.220 --> 48:18.195 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the art world, counseling
individual, corporate
and institutional clients.

48:18.229 --> 48:22.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kerri Hurtado is an adviser with
San Francisco's
Artsouce.

48:22.500 --> 48:30.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At Untitled, she showed works to
Jaya Kader,
a Miami-based architect who
designs homes

48:30.107 --> 48:32.143 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with contemporary art in mind.

48:32.176 --> 48:35.012 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAYA KADER, Architect: You get
exposed to
so much.

48:35.045 --> 48:41.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's no way that -- it would
take you a
whole year to get to see as much
as you get

48:41.419 --> 48:45.456 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to see in a few days in Miami.

48:45.489 --> 48:50.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I like to work with Artsouce
because the
art world is so vast.

48:50.728 --> 48:55.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Art everywhere,
but also other
kinds of excess.

48:55.399 --> 48:57.168 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Art journalist Janelle Zara.

48:57.201 --> 49:01.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANELLE ZARA, Journalist:
Because we're in
Miami, things sometimes get a
little out of

49:01.272 --> 49:02.239 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
hand.

49:02.273 --> 49:03.707 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's a lot of showiness, you
know?

49:03.741 --> 49:05.543 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Everyone in the world is here.

49:05.576 --> 49:10.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so that involves a lot of
fancy cars,
a lot of dressing up, you know,
a lot of hopping

49:10.147 --> 49:11.916 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from party to party.

49:11.949 --> 49:15.252 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, increasingly, people who
are not in the
art world want to participate.

49:15.286 --> 49:21.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But even in what
Zara described
as a subdued year, possibly
owing to the Zika

49:22.026 --> 49:28.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
scare, the spectacle went on, a
psychedelic
electronic dance party in
Collins Park, complete

49:28.699 --> 49:36.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with a robot bouncer, droning
guitars played
by women standing on amplifiers,
and burgers

49:36.207 --> 49:39.343 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
grilled under the hood of a
limousine.

49:39.376 --> 49:43.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There were the behind-the-scenes
dinners and
parties galore.

49:43.514 --> 49:49.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also on display, the rise of
homegrown museums
and collectors like the Rubell
family, who

49:49.553 --> 49:55.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
during the Art Basel fair, held
an opening
in their own enormous private
collection space.

49:55.893 --> 49:58.195 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You're market makers in a sense,
right?

49:58.229 --> 50:01.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you choose an artist, you
have the power
to make people.

50:01.365 --> 50:06.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MERA RUBELL, Rubell Family
Collection: I know
people say that all the time,
that we make

50:06.770 --> 50:12.309 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
markets and stuff like -- but I
can tell you
that that's not the way we live
our life.

50:12.343 --> 50:14.578 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We don't wake up in the morning
and say, oh,
we make markets.

50:14.612 --> 50:16.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is really like the outside
world.

50:16.046 --> 50:17.181 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The inside world is very, very
basic.

50:17.214 --> 50:21.252 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a family that is constantly
talking about
the art.

50:21.285 --> 50:24.555 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have the privilege to curate
it and hang
it.

50:24.588 --> 50:26.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The market is not so interesting
to us.

50:26.323 --> 50:31.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The growth of art
fairs has
given more buyers access to the
art world,

50:31.195 --> 50:33.464 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
less power to auction houses.

50:33.497 --> 50:39.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's a strict hierarchy
here, several
tiers of VIPs who get in first,
ahead of the

50:39.470 --> 50:41.305 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
general public.

50:41.338 --> 50:45.910 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Most of the work here is
actually sold before
the fair even opens to the
public.

50:45.943 --> 50:49.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clare McAndrew is a cultural
economist who
studies the art market.

50:49.146 --> 50:53.284 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CLARE MCANDREW, Cultural
Economist: The high
end has done extremely well.

50:53.317 --> 50:59.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, I looked at auction
sales, for example,
and the segment over a million
has grown about

50:59.623 --> 51:01.225 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
400 percent over the last 10
years.

51:01.258 --> 51:04.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you look at the segment over
$10 million,
it's grown at over 1000 percent.

51:04.728 --> 51:07.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And if you look at the lower-end
segments,
they have grown very slowly.

51:07.865 --> 51:11.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In terms of sales growth, it's a
very top-heavy
marketplace.

51:11.769 --> 51:16.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But that sort of
fits with
the whole inequality discussion
we have politically.

51:16.440 --> 51:21.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLARE MCANDREW: It's exactly
paralleling what's
happening in the wider economy
and in wealth

51:21.679 --> 51:23.480 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
distribution.

51:23.514 --> 51:27.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And, as with
other markets,
those with the best information
gain advantage.

51:27.151 --> 51:31.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Josh Baer is an art adviser who
writes the
industry newsletter "Baer Faxt."

51:31.288 --> 51:35.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSH BAER, "Baer Faxt": Having
more information
about who's doing the show at
the Tate or

51:35.259 --> 51:39.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who's going to be in the Whitney
Biennial
or whose work is sold out and
who's buying

51:39.496 --> 51:42.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it or what's going on gives you
momentum information.

51:42.967 --> 51:46.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Momentum, which
you can take
to clients or others and say...

51:46.904 --> 51:51.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSH BAER: Time to buy now
because next year
it's going to be twice as much
and there's

51:51.041 --> 51:53.277 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going to be something else going
on.

51:53.310 --> 51:54.645 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Art fairs are like auctions.

51:54.678 --> 51:56.580 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're about forced urgency.

51:56.613 --> 52:02.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're about the illusion of
you better decide
in the next 20 seconds, because
some billionaire

52:02.486 --> 52:06.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from China is coming in two
minutes and he
may take what you want.

52:06.090 --> 52:11.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Amid all the
buying and selling,
what's an up-and-coming artist
to do, especially

52:11.662 --> 52:17.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
one like Hank Willis Thomas, who
works in
many different media, often
tackling difficult

52:17.301 --> 52:19.670 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
political issues of the moment?

52:19.703 --> 52:24.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says artists need to imagine
a better future
for society, even if part of the
present deal

52:24.808 --> 52:26.276 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
here is lucrative.

52:26.310 --> 52:28.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HANK WILLIS THOMAS, Artist: So,
there's no
way to get out of this system.

52:28.846 --> 52:33.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What I'm really most interested
in is how
we can use the system to improve
it.

52:33.851 --> 52:35.652 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's always a positive
improvement.

52:35.686 --> 52:38.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't want to alienate myself
from anyone.

52:38.222 --> 52:42.559 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A bit more
politics and smaller
crowds this year.

52:42.593 --> 52:47.264 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But sales, the true bottom line,
were said
to be holding steady.

